nt to power, called on Monday for early elections after a curfew was announced in the capital Baghdad. Source: Reuters Vanguard News The death toll in anti-government protests that have swept Iraq the past four days has soared to at least 44, security and medical sources say. The figure has nearly doubled in the past 24 hours, as clashes between protesters and police intensified. The military said "unidentified snipers" had killed four… October 5, 2019 In "Foreign" Police snipers shot at demonstrators on Saturday killing five people and several others wounded in a resumption of anti-government unrest in Eastern Baghdad. October 6, 2019 In "News" At least three protesters and one policeman have been killed in Iraq's southern city of Nasiriyah, according to a monitoring group, after nationwide anti-government protests devolved into violence that saw security forces fire live rounds and tear gas for a second straight day. The unrest on Wednesday came a day… October 3, 2019 In "Foreign"